## 19. Year/Tax Year Conventions

- UK tax year: 6 April to 5 April → "2026/27" = 6 April 2026 to 5 April 2027
- "2026/26" is **INVALID** — never use
- Tax year topics (self-assessment, pension, rates): use "2026/27"
- Calendar year topics (MTD deadline, VAT threshold): use "2026"
- Evergreen topics: no year needed
